Thyroid Function Test.description:
The thyroid is a small gland located in the lower-front part of your neck. Thyroid function test measures how well your thyroid gland is working. This includes measuring the levels of Thyroid hormone and Thyroid Stimulating Hormone.How does Thyroid Function Test work?
A specialist physician will locate the brachial tendon using a standard clinical hammer. A specialized spring loaded reflex hammer is then cocked and placed on the tendon on the surface of skin by pushing a button. The attached sensing device detects the length of time the brachioradialis muscle relaxes after it contracts. The software combines the actual results, the previously answered questionnaire and other lab findings to come up with figures that represent the thyroid gland performance and recommend bioidentical hormones to correct deficiencies and imbalances.Is the treatment painful? Is it safe? How long will the treatment take?
