Vascular System Analysis.description:
A vascular systemic analysis is a non-invasive imaging examination that allows a physician to conduct a hemodynamic analysis of coronary blood flow and function based on parameters like the stiffness of the arterial walls of the heart and the vessels. Not only does this assist the physician in early diagnosis of Cardiovascular diseases, it gives a detailed account of the effects the current lifestyle, eating habits and smoking on vascular function.How does Vascular System Analysis work?
Everlast uses a state-of-the-art scanning and imagining machine with a clipper that attaches to the index finger and displays resulting analysis on a screen for the interpretation of the doctor.Is the treatment painful? Is it safe? How long will the treatment take?
The procedure in completely non-invasive and pain-free. The clipper gently grabs the finger between two prongs and allows for a quick 2 minute analysis. {"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Vascular System Analysis work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":" Everlast uses a state-of-the-art scanning and imagining machine with a clipper that attaches to the index finger and displays resulting analysis on a screen for the interpretation of the doctor."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the treatment painful? Is it safe? How long will the treatment take?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":" The procedure in completely non-invasive and pain-free. The clipper gently grabs the finger between two prongs and allows for a quick 2 minute analysis."}}]}

